cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to source identification, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of machine learning techniques to make decisions based on training data suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and learning (cs.LG). Finally, the study of the impact of corrupted training data on the performance of the defender is related to statistical learning theory (cs.SI).
